   "source": [
    "# **Example**: Optimizers Benchmarking\n",
    "\n",
    "Sample code for how to benchmark Optimizers for different modalities.\n",
    "You might have to fiddle with the batch size to get the highest numbers for your environment.\n",
    "\n",
   ]
  },
    {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Images\n",
    "Benchmarking a ViT-S model on 224x224 images. Results are in im/s.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Note**: I'm using AdamW(ViT-S) here as a example, you should shift to specific optimizers and models"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "75.196"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 1,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "!python train_wandb.py \\\n",
    "    --model vit_small_patch16_224 \\\n",
    "    --input-size 3 224 224 \\\n",
    "    --sched cosine -j 8 --epochs 100 \\\n",
    "    --opt AdamW --lr 1e-3 \\\n",
    "    --opt-betas 0.9 0.999 --opt-eps 1e-8 \\\n",
    "    --weight-decay 5e-2 --warmup-lr 1e-9 \\\n",
    "    -b 128 --amp \\\n",
    "    --color-jitter 0 --aug-repeats 0 \\\n",
    "    --log-wandb --wandb-project vit_small_patch16_224_optim_eval \\\n",
    "    --warmup-epochs 5 --aa rand-m9-mstd0.5-inc1 \\\n",
    "    --smoothing 0.1 --remode pixel \\\n",
    "    --crop-pct 0.875 --reprob 0.25 \\\n",
    "    --drop 0.0 --drop-path 0.1 \\\n",
    "    --mixup 0.8 --cutmix 1.0 \\\n",
    "    --output runs --experiment vit_AdamW \\\n",
    "    --torchcompile inductor"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## NLP\n",
